    "narrative": "For our April 23rd slate, **Corbin Carroll** leads the charge with an elite 85.93 score. He is the must-start of the day, buoyed by a favorable matchup against Davis Martin and a premium #2 spot in the order that maximizes his stolen base potential\u2014the lifeblood of our Roto strategy. Close behind, **Mickey Moniak** (75.97) provides massive value at a discount. His high score is driven by a juicy matchup against the porous arm of Matt Waldron; the combination of a 14% park boost and the aggressive #2 spot makes **Mickey Moniak** a secondary engine for our efficiency targets today. **Jose Caballero** also warrants attention, as his 67.92 score is significantly inflated by an advantageous platoon edge against the lefty Payton Tolle, demonstrating why we prioritize these matchup-specific swings in our lineup construction.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Brice Turang**, who finished with a 46.56, narrowly missing the cut. While his elite sprint speed and stolen base utility are historically vital, his matchup against a high-tier arm like Skubal (2.71 xERA) effectively neutralized the efficiency gains we seek for our daily game cap management. Consequently, we are opting to prioritize the higher raw output from our mid-tier infielders. We continue to monitor the status of **Dalton Rushing** and **Luis Campusano**, whose scores are currently tempered by the \"Lineup Pending\" designation. **Dalton Rushing** carries the most inherent risk today, as a negative park factor compounded by a tough matchup against Logan Webb keeps him near our floor, necessitating a close watch for any late-breaking lineup changes that might further compress his value.",
